article.headline: Arkansas State 66, New Orleans 44
article.story:
JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Adrianne Davie scored 14 points and
pulled down nine rebounds Monday night as Arkansas State topped New
Orleans 66-44 in a Sun Belt Conference matchup.

ASU (13-8, 6-2 SBC) made nearly half its field-goal attempts,
while UNO hit less than a third of its shots.

UNO (1-20, 1-8) trailed 36-19 at the halft.

Le'Della English provided most of the offense for the Lady
Privateers, scoring 20 points. April Eason added 11 points, but no
other UNO player had more than 4 points.

Rudy Sims was the only other ASU player in double digits.
